This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing and hate speech detection. It may also belong to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as it deals with online hate speech. Additionally, it could belong to cs.CY (Computers and Society) as it deals with the societal impact of hate speech. It may also belong to cs.SD (Software Engineering) as it proposes two types of hate speech detection models. Finally, it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it uses logistic regression and neural network models for hate speech detection.
